  "section_name": "Risk Analysis",
  "text": "Financial performance volatility presents a material risk for Airbnb. Operating margin fluctuated significantly across recent quarters, declining from 40.86% in Q3 2024 to 1.67% in Q1 2025 before recovering to 19.77% in Q2 2025 [C020, C013, C006]. Net income showed similar volatility, dropping from $1,368,000,000 in Q3 2024 to $154,000,000 in Q1 2025, then rising to $642,000,000 in Q2 2025 [C021, C014, C007]. This earnings variability suggests sensitivity to seasonal travel patterns and macroeconomic conditions affecting discretionary spending, which could complicate financial forecasting and investor confidence.",
